3 681A.020 1. “Casualty insurance” includes:
4 (a) Vehicle insurance. Insurance against loss of or damage to
5 any land vehicle or aircraft or any draft or riding animal or to
6 property while contained therein or thereon or being loaded or
7 unloaded therein or therefrom, from any hazard or cause, and
8 against any loss, liability or expense resulting from or incidental to
9 ownership, maintenance or use of any such vehicle, aircraft or
10 animal, together with insurance against accidental injury to natural
11 persons, irrespective of legal liability of the insured, including the
12 named insured, while in, entering, alighting from, adjusting,
13 repairing, cranking, or caused by being struck by a vehicle, aircraft
14 or draft or riding animal, if such insurance is issued as an incidental
15 part of insurance on the vehicle, aircraft or draft or riding animal.
16 (b) Liability insurance. Insurance against legal liability for the
17 death, injury or disability of any human being, or for damage to
18 property, including liability resulting from negligence in rendering
19 expert, fiduciary or professional services, and provisions of medical,
20 hospital, surgical, disability benefits to injured persons and funeral
21 and death benefits to dependents, beneficiaries or personal
22 representatives of persons killed, irrespective of legal liability of the
23 insured, when issued as an incidental coverage with or supplemental
24 to liability insurance.
25 (c) Workers’ compensation and employer’s liability. Insurance
26 of the obligations accepted by, imposed upon or assumed by
27 employers under law for death, disablement or injury of employees.
28 (d) Burglary and theft. Insurance against loss or damage by
29 burglary, theft, larceny, robbery, forgery, fraud, vandalism,
30 malicious mischief, confiscation, or wrongful conversion, disposal
31 or concealment, or from any attempt at any of the foregoing,
32 including supplemental coverage for medical, hospital, surgical and
33 funeral expense incurred by the named insured or any other person
34 as a result of bodily injury during the commission of a burglary,
35 robbery or theft by another, and, also, insurance against loss of or
36 damage to moneys, coins, bullion, securities, notes, drafts,
37 acceptances or any other valuable papers and documents, resulting
38 from any cause.
39 (e) Personal property floater. Insurance upon personal effects
40 against loss or damage from any cause.
41 (f) Glass. Insurance against loss or damage to glass, including its
42 lettering, ornamentation and fittings.
